ohu
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:formerly, a state-sponsored, rural commune. -->a kibbutz-type of landed-community introduced by the Labour Government in the 1970s; a communal work group
Origin:Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
